---

## 1. Header (Navigation Bar)

This section is the main navigation bar at the top of the page.

* **Main Element:** `<header>`
* **Key Class:** `navbar`
* **Sub-components:**
    * `div.logo`: Contains the logo `<img>` and "PingMe" text.
    * `div.nav-links`: The main container for navigation buttons.
        * **ID:** `nav-links` (likely used by JavaScript to show/hide the menu on mobile).
    * `div.nav-buttons`: A wrapper for the login/signup buttons.
        * `button.btn.login`: The "Log In" button.
        * `button.btn.signup`: The "Sign Up" button.
    * `i.dark-mode-toggle`: The moon icon to toggle dark mode.
        * **ID:** `dark-mode-toggle` (used by JavaScript).
    * `i.hamburger`: The hamburger menu icon (for mobile).
        * **ID:** `hamburger` (used by JavaScript).

---

## 2. Description ("Hero" Section)

This is the main "hero" section at the top, designed to grab the user's attention.

* **Main Element:** `<section>`
* **Key Class:** `description`
* **Sub-components:**
    * `div.description-text`: A wrapper holding the text content.
    * `<h1>`: The main headline: "Message privately, connect freely."
    * `<p>`: The sub-headline or description.
    * `button.btn.signup`: The main "Sign Up" call-to-action button.

---

## 3. Features Section

This section is a grid that lists the key features of the application.

* **Main Element:** `<section>`
* **Key Class:** `features`
* **Sub-components:**
    * This section contains **6 identical** `div.feature-box` elements.
    * **Structure of each `div.feature-box`:**
        * `<i>`: A Font Awesome icon (e.g., `fas.fa-comment-dots`).
        * `<h3>`: The feature title (e.g., "Fast Messaging").
        * `<p>`: A short description of the feature.

---

## 4. How It Works Section

This section provides a simple 3-step guide on how to get started.

* **Main Element:** `<section>`
* **Key Class:** `how-it-works`
* **Sub-components:**
    * `h2.section-title`: The main title for this section.
    * `div.steps-container`: A flex or grid container holding the steps.
    * This container has **3 identical** `div.step` elements.
    * **Structure of each `div.step`:**
        * `<i>`: A Font Awesome icon with the `step-icon` class.
        * `<h3>`: The step title (e.g., "1. Create Account").
        * `<p>`: A short description of the step.

---

## 5. Testimonials Section

This section displays social proof using cards with user quotes.

* **Main Element:** `<section>`
* **Key Class:** `testimonials`
* **Sub-components:**
    * `h2.section-title`: The main title for this section.
    * `div.testimonial-grid`: A container for the testimonial cards.
    * This grid contains **2 identical** `div.testimonial-card` elements.
    * **Structure of each `div.testimonial-card`:**
        * `<p>`: The user's quote.
        * `div.testimonial-author`: A wrapper for the author's info.
            * `<img>`: The author's profile picture.
            * `<div>`: A text wrapper holding:
                * `<strong>`: The author's name.
                * `<small>`: The author's title or job.

---

## 6. Footer

This is the final section at the bottom of the page.

* **Main Element:** `<footer>`
* **Key Class:** `footer`
* **Sub-components:**
    * `div.logo`: Re-uses the `logo` class from the header.
    * `<p>`: The copyright text.
    * `div.social-links`: A wrapper for social media icons.
        * `<a>`: Anchor tags wrapping Font Awesome `<i>` icons (e.g., `fab.fa-twitter`).

---

## Assets & Scripts

These are the non-visible files loaded in the `<head>` and at the end of the `<body>`.

* **Fonts:**
    * Google Fonts (`Poppins`)
    * Font Awesome (for icons)
* **CSS:**
    * `/css/page.css`: Your custom stylesheet that defines all the classes above.
* **JavaScript:**
    * `/js/page.js`: The script that will handle the hamburger menu, dark mode, and any other interactions.